CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 8, 1963, pg. 13, reads: "'Miss Fairview Park' - Miss Audrey Sayles, seated center, representing Macedonia Baptist Church, Duquesne, Pa., was crowned 'Miss Fairview Park' at the seventh annual May Festival, for the benefit of Fairview Park, which took place at Rodman Street Baptist Church, recently. Edward Coles, president of the Mon Valley Sunday School Association, sponsoring unit; and Barbara Bush, general chairman, stand behind the honoree. Other contestants, left to right are, Sandra [illegible] ...del of the Askew family; [ill.] of Sixth Mt. Zion; Valerie Dupree of Second Baptist, Homestead, second place runner-up; Olivetta Simms of Rodman Street Church, first place runner-up; Junyetta Jelks of Trinity AME Church and [ill.] Hodge of Ebenezer Baptist, Pittsburgh. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: "Miss Fairview Park" Audrey Sayles wearing tiara and seated in center, surrounded by other contestants and officials including Edward Coles, Barbara Bush, Valerie Dupree, Olivetta Simms, Junyetta Jelks, and others, at Rodman Street Baptist Church
